gas /ɡæs/

(gassing,gassed,gasses,gases) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Gas is a substance like air that is neither liquid nor solid and burns easily. It is used as a fuel for cooking and heating. 煤气 

例： Coal is actually cheaper than gas. 煤炭实际上比煤气便宜。 

2. N-VAR A gas is any substance that is neither liquid nor solid, for example oxygen or hydrogen. 气体 

例： Helium is a very light gas. 氦是一种很轻的气体。 

3. N-MASS Gas is a poisonous gas that can be used as a weapon. 毒气 

例： The problem was that the exhaust gases contain many toxins. 问题是废气含有很多毒素。 

4. N-UNCOUNT Gas is the same as . 汽油 [美国英语] 

5. V-T To gas a person or animal means to kill them by making them breathe poisonous gas. 用毒气杀死 

例： Her husband ran a pipe from her car exhaust to the bedroom in an attempt to gas her. 她丈夫将一根管子从她的汽车排气管导入卧室，试图用毒气杀死她。 

6.  →  see also gas mask , greenhouse gas , tear gas

